 Given a quantum interval-valued probability measure
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\mu}:\events\rightarrow\mathscr{I}$
\end_inset

: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A 
\emph on
core
\emph default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\mu}$
\end_inset

 is the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{core}\left(\bar{\mu}\right)=\set{\pmeas:\events\rightarrow[0,1]}{\forall P\in\events.~\pmeas\left(P\right)\in\bar{\mu}\left(P\right)}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\mu}$
\end_inset

 is called convex if 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\mu}\left(P_{0}\vee P_{1}\right)+\bar{\mu}\left(P_{0}P_{1}\right)\subseteq\bar{\mu}\left(P_{0}\right)+\bar{\mu}\left(P_{1}\right)$
\end_inset

 for all commuting 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{0},P_{1}\in\events$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

